title: Coronado National Memorial: Trees and Shrubs
body: Explore This Park    Learn About the Park     Nature     Plants     Trees and Shrubs                Trees and Shrubs         Mexican blue oak leaves with acorns. (Photo by David Bly)  The upper portion of the Memorial is predominately oak woodlands with some areas of Mexican pinyon and alligator juniper. Along ephemeral drainages are Arizona sycamore and walnut trees, canyon grape vines, and other species typical of riparian areas.
